---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home Renovation Loan - Fund Repairs & Remodeling | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Home Renovation Loan</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Home Renovation Loan</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Transform your home with a renovation loan for repairs, remodeling, interior design, and structural improvements. Borrow from ₹1 lakh to ₹50 lakhs with interest rates starting at 8.75% p.a. Enjoy tax benefits under Section 24(b) on the interest paid.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i>
          <span>Loan Amount: ₹1L - ₹50L</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-calendar-days"></i>
          <span>Tenure: 1-15 Years</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Interest: 8.75% onwards</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>What is a Home Renovation Loan?</h2>
          <p>A home renovation loan is a specialized financing product designed to fund repairs, remodeling, structural modifications, and interior design of your existing residential property. Unlike personal loans, home renovation loans offer lower interest rates (comparable to home loans) because they are typically secured against the property being renovated. Common uses include kitchen and bathroom remodeling, roof repair, painting, flooring, plumbing, electrical rewiring, and adding new rooms or floors.</p>
          <p>TrueCred Loan Expert partners with over 30 banks and HFCs to bring you the best home renovation loan offers. Our platform helps you calculate the renovation cost, choose the right loan amount and tenure, and compare interest rates — all in one place. Home renovation loans also offer tax benefits under Section 24(b) where interest up to ₹30,000 per year (₹2 lakhs if the loan is from the original home loan lender as a top-up) is deductible from your taxable income.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">8.75%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Interest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹50 Lakh</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Loan Amount</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">15 Years</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Tenure</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Home Renovation Loan Rates — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>SBI</td>
                <td>8.75% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Ltd</td>
                <td>9.00% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>9.25% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 1.00%</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Bank of Baroda</td>
                <td>8.90% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>PNB Housing</td>
                <td>9.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 1.00%</td>
                <td>12 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Property owner with clear title and ownership documents</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Property should be residential and free from legal disputes</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Applicant aged between 23 and 60 years (65 for self-employed)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Minimum monthly income of ₹20,000 for salaried applicants</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> CIBIL score of 700 or above for best interest rates</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Renovation estimate from a licensed contractor or architect</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Get a Home Renovation Loan</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Plan Your Renovation</h4>
              <p>Get a detailed estimate of renovation costs from a contractor. Include materials, labour, permits, and a 10% contingency buffer.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Check Eligibility</h4>
              <p>Enter your income, property value, and renovation budget to check eligibility across 30+ banks and HFCs on TrueCred.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Submit Property Documents</h4>
              <p>Provide property ownership proof, renovation plan, and cost estimate along with your income and KYC documents.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Get Funds & Renovate</h4>
              <p>Loan disbursed in 1-2 tranches based on renovation progress. Transform your home while paying manageable EMIs.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Property ownership documents — sale deed, registry, and mutation certificate</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Renovation cost estimate from licensed contractor or architect</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Building plan approval from local municipal authority (for structural changes)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Identity and address proof — Aadhaar, PAN, and passport-size photographs</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Income proof — salary slips, ITR, and bank statements for last 6 months</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Existing home loan details (if applicable) for top-up consideration</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Apply for Renovation Loan</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Loan Amount</option>
                  <option value="100000">₹1,00,000</option>
                  <option value="200000">₹2,00,000</option>
                  <option value="500000">₹5,00,000</option>
                  <option value="1000000">₹10,00,000</option>
                  <option value="2000000">₹20,00,000</option>
                  <option value="3000000">₹30,00,000</option>
                  <option value="5000000">₹50,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Score</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Insurance</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Common questions about home renovation loans.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Is a home renovation loan different from a home improvement loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              These terms are often used interchangeably. However, some banks differentiate: a 'renovation loan' covers structural changes (adding rooms, floors, major repairs) while a 'home improvement loan' covers cosmetic upgrades (painting, flooring, fixtures). Both are available from TrueCred partners at similar rates. Check with the specific lender for what's covered under their product.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I get tax benefits on a home renovation loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, interest paid on a home renovation loan is tax-deductible under Section 24(b) of the Income Tax Act. For a standalone renovation loan, the deduction is limited to ₹30,000 per year. If the renovation loan is taken as a top-up on your existing home loan, the interest deduction goes up to ₹2 lakhs (combined with home loan interest). Principal repayment qualifies under Section 80C up to ₹1.5 lakhs.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What renovation work is covered under this loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Home renovation loans cover a wide range of work including: kitchen and bathroom remodeling, painting and waterproofing, flooring replacement, plumbing and electrical rewiring, roof repair and terrace waterproofing, room addition or extension, window and door replacement, interior design and furnishing, swimming pool or garden landscaping, and installation of solar panels or rainwater harvesting. Non-movable improvements to the property are generally covered.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How much renovation loan can I get?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              The loan amount depends on the renovation cost estimate, property value, your income, and existing loan obligations. Typically, you can get up to 80-90% of the renovation cost or 50-60% of the current property market value, whichever is lower. Maximum amounts range from ₹10 lakhs (unsecured) to ₹50 lakhs (secured against property). A detailed cost estimate from a contractor helps maximize the approved amount.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Should I take a home renovation loan or a personal loan for renovation?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              A home renovation loan is almost always better due to: lower interest rate (8.75% vs 11%+ for personal loans), longer repayment tenure (up to 15 years vs 5 years), higher loan amount, and tax benefits on interest. The only downside is that renovation loans require property documentation and take longer to process (7-10 days vs 2-3 days for personal loans). For small renovations under ₹2 lakhs, a personal loan might be more convenient.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Finance Your Dream Home Makeover</h3>
          <p>Get renovation loans from ₹1L to ₹50L at home loan rates. Enjoy tax benefits and flexible repayment.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline" style="color:#fff;border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);padding:14px 32px;font-size:0.95rem;">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
